OL,3,CPrime Minister promises to clamp down
OL,4,Con retail crime
OL,6,F"Our local shops are the lifeblood of
OL,7,Four communities, and they must be free
OL,8,Fto trade without the threat of crime
OL,9,For abuse."
OL,11,FThe new offence will carry a maximum
OL,12,Fsentence of six months' imprisonment
OL,13,For an unlimited fine, the same
OL,14,Fsentence for the existing offence of
OL,15,Fcommon assault.
OL,17,FRepeat offenders could also be forced
OL,18,Fto wear an electronic tag, as could
OL,19,Fconsistent shoplifters, under
OL,20,Famendments to the Bill currently
OL,21,Fmaking its way through Parliament.
